  "response": "The term \"android\" has a few meanings:\n\n1. In robotics and science fiction, an android is a robot that closely resembles a human in appearance and behavior, typically with human-like features and the ability to interact like a person.\n\n2. In technology, Android is also the name of a mobile operating system developed by Google, which is used on smartphones, tablets, and other mobile devices. This Android OS is based on a modified version of the Linux kernel and other open-source software.\n\n3. Etymologically, the word \"android\" comes from the Greek words \"andro-\" meaning \"male\" and \"-eides\" meaning \"like\" or \"resembling,\" so it literally translates to \"man-like\" or \"resembling a human.\"",
